name: RtmpStreamingErrorCode
description: Error codes of the RTMP or RTMPS streaming.

parameters.OK: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming publishes successfully.

parameters.InvalidParameters: Invalid argument used. Please check the parameter setting. For example, if you do not call setLiveTranscoding to set the transcoding parameters before calling addPublishStreamUrl, the SDK returns this error.

parameters.EncryptedStreamNotAllowed: Check whether you set the parameters in the setLiveTranscoding method properly.

parameters.ConnectionTimeout: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming is encrypted and cannot be published. Call addPublishStreamUrl to re-publish the stream.

parameters.InternalServerError: An error occurs in Agora's streaming server. Call the addPublishStreamUrl method to publish the streaming again.

parameters.RtmpServerError: An error occurs in the CDN server.

parameters.TooOften: The RTMP or RTMPS streaming publishes too frequently.

parameters.ReachLimit: The host has published more than 10 URLs. Delete the unnecessary URLs before adding new ones.

parameters.NotAuthorized: The host manipulates other hosts' streams. For example, the host updates or stops other hosts' streams. Check your app logic.

parameters.StreamNotFound: Agora's server fails to find the RTMP or RTMPS streaming.

parameters.FormatNotSupported: The URL format is incorrect. Check whether the URL format is correct.
